<br>
<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
/Expeditionary Force report #345-A<br>
Area of operation: The Ferrott<br>
Objective: Marsh bear<br>
Att: Captain Compolten.<br>
<br>
<br>
Greetings Captain Compolten.<br>
<br>
I write to you with a bit of mixed news. On our recent expedition with our beloved Zoo-keeper, we ventured into the marshy Ferrott, a rather dangerous area filled with Ogres, Lizards and worse. <br>
Coldhaine, our Zoo-keeper, was specific on getting a certain type of bears living in these lands, a so called Marsh Bear, to add to the rather extensive collection of beasts in our Zoo. So we headed out with a small but well-equipped expeditionary force comprising of me, ensign Trimanus, the Half-elf guide Strongbranch, Coldhaine and our ally from the Eldrich Collective, the Wizard named Panlounimos.<br>
The Wizard made sure our travels were short and managed to teleport us near to the area were Coldhaine expected to find the largest numbers of Marsh Bears, and luckily we made into the Ferrott without much trouble as we kept a low-profile and travelled by nightfall. <br>
<br>
We were very cautious as we entered the Ferrott and remained on guard at all times, just as you have taught us. And surely enough after scouting ahead of us, Strongbranch managed to locate an isolated Marsh Bear that seemed large and particularly vicious. Just what Coldhaine had wanted for the collection of beasts. <br>
We managed to rather quickly overpower the Marsh Bear with our nets and the specially tinkered cage-contraption Tinipus made for Coldhaine years ago. All went well, we got it towed back to the waiting Panlounimus, and he began to prepare the cantrip to get us back to safety, when all hell broke loose. <br>
Out from the green haze that hangs over the entire swamp, an enormous Ogre charged us with a set of claws and a ferociousness unmatched by any beast I have met before. As the Ogre were slashing left and right, the bear seemed to gain a surge of strenght and started to snap the bars of its cage, just as Panlounimos spoke the final words of the spell, magic whirled around us and we found us back in the Forest near the Steamfronts...Fortunately this event seemed to have confused the Ogre and bear quite alot, so we siezed the initiative and decided to retreat as fast as possible.<br>
Trinamus, Coldhaine and Panlounimos towed the cage, while me and Strongbranch covered the rear making certain the Ogre would not follow us. I personally saw Strongbranch fire what must have been a dozen arrows swiftly into this beast, almost before I could react, and the Ogre fell before us. To make sure it was dead, a couple more arrows were fired at the bleeding body of the Ogre, and we rushed as quickly as we could back through the Forest and into the Steamfront mountains.<br>
<br>
As I caught up with the others, the Wizard had managed to strenghten the cage with his Magic and the beast seemed much less aggressive as it have lost sight of the Ogre, but I fear that in the moment of chaos before the teleport was completed the Ogre managed to give Trimanus a deep wound in the chest.<br>
<br>
We made it home in one piece and with the objective we set out to capture, but I must recommend as strongly as I can, that ensign Trimanus be rewarded a medal of bravery and a good months vacation. I hope you will look kindly upon my request.<br>
<br>
<br>
Signing off<br>
Expeditionary Leader - Rangal Denbarious<br>
<br>
Note : Next time I would suggest that you try to talk Coldhaine into settling for a more peaceful beast for the Zoo. As proud as I am of it, I cannot help but dread the day, we loose a Gemchopper because Coldhaine have unrealistic expectations.<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
/Guard report 562-BH<br>
Area of operation: The Ak'Anon Zoo.<br>
Objective: Regular guard duties.<br>
Att: Captain Compolten.<br>
<br>
Greetings Captain Compolten.<br>
<br>
I bring bad news, as I fear the old saying that, one ill event seldom comes alone, holds true in this case.<br>
Some time during the night, a beast of an Ogre have managed to, somehow, slip past the outer guards, and travel inside Ak'Anon. As if this is not dreadful enough, it have managed to find its way to the Zoo where it broke in and started to free the Marsh bear that we recently captured in the Ferrott. (See report #345-A)<br>
Coldhaine the Zoo-keeper woke up from loud noices coming from the Zoo, and he proceeded to sneak down there only see the Ogre, that we had ran into on our expedition. Wisely enough he contacted me immidiately, and me and Haritiom rushed down there to stop the beasts from unleashing untold havoc on a sleeping Ak'Anon. <br>
I ordered Coldhaine to go and wake more Gemchoppers and send them to the Zoo at once. While he was away we tried our best to keep the Ogre and the Marsh bear trapped inside the Zoo, untill we could get reinforcements to overpower both of them. Upon seeing us the Ogre charged us, fierce fighting errupted and we tried our best to stand ground. <br>
Only in the nick of time did Coldhaine return with more guards, as the beast had already torn Haritiom to shreds and was turning its attention towards me. With the help of 3 other guards we managed to force the Ogre to retreat down to the tunnels underneath the Zoo. Coldhaine, being always on the look out for the most vicious beasts to add to the Zoo collection, rushed into his personal quaters and brought forth a dart-shooting device of this own creation. <br>
He ensured us that he could take care of the Ogre, if we could just corner it and hold it at bay for a moment, and seeing that Coldhaine have managed to surprise us countless times before with his tinkerings, we proceeded down into the lower tunnels.<br>
Fortunately for us the Ogre had ran into one of the old service tunnels leading to a dead-end, so we had it cornered and were ready to strike it dead, should it try to charge us. Upon seeing it, Coldhaine pulled the lever of his device and shot a dart into the beast. Seemingly the dart had been dipped in some of his special concogtions and the enormous Ogre fell to the ground almost instantly.<br>
<br>
We inspected the body and it was still breathing, though completely paralyzed, and an arugement broke out since Coldhaine insisted that we kept the beast for study and eventually to be displayed in the Zoo, while the rest of the guards argued that we slay it right there. <br>
Feeling grateful that Coldhaine had saved us for what could have been a rather nasty battle, I chose to grant him his wish and we dragged the body to the strongest cage we had, and put it in shackles.<br>
<br>
I know that Coldhaine have sent a plea to the King, suggesting that we keep the beast, but I must admit that I had regrets on not killing this foul creation when we had the chance. So I will write a letter to the King suggesting that we kill it, if not for Ak'Anon's own security, then for the retribution of Haritioms death.<br>
I hope you will support me in this case, Captain.<br>
<br>
<br>
I shall report back to you tomorrow, or as soon as we hear from the King.<br>
<br>
Signing off<br>
Guard Sergeant - Rangal Denbarious<br>
